    <h1>Sequences and Limits</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Jiří Lebl · <a href="https://www.jirka.org/ra/">Basic Analysis I, Ch. 2</a> · CC BY-SA 4.0</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A sequence converges to L if, for every &epsilon; &gt; 0, all but finitely many terms lie within &epsilon; of L. Completeness guarantees that every bounded monotone sequence converges and every Cauchy sequence converges.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Sequence converging to a limit -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 180" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Axes -->
